overview: News 31s on Virgin Cross Country Train – 31s on engineering – Fragonset 31s, 66s and 47s on Swindon to Longbridge Cars – 66s new to traffic – D9000 in South London – Class 33 on East Lancs – 73s on engineering and stone traffic – Freightliner 57 in traffic - D9000 to Plymouth including the Lickey Incline – Railfreight 47s in decline – 47 033 at Reading – Diesel Miscellany with 37, 56 and 58 haulage – Livery Changes – D6700 on Charter – HST on West Somerset Railway – D900 on Chester charter – GWR liveried 47 – Double headed 31s on Binliner – Blackburn redevelopment – MOD working to Dereham – 37s on West Country China Clay – New duties for 66s – Midland Diesel Gala.
